                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Nitish to do a Barbighi in Rajgir
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Patna, Dec. 20: Nothing succeeds like success.        
	Nitish Kumar, for the first time in the states history, organised a cabinet meeting at remote Barbighi village in north Bihars Begusarai Lok Sabha constituency as part of his government on peoples doorstep programme ahead of the last Lok Sabha polls.        
	The move paid off with the NDA bagging 33 of 40 Lok Sabha seats, including Begusarai. The observers described the grand NDA show a result of Nitish establishing direct connect with the masses.        
	Nitish has decided to welcome the New Year, also the Assembly election year in Bihar, while staying at Rajgir from December 25 to 31. He will return to Patna on January 1. In course of his Rajgir sojourn, the chief minister will organise a cabinet meeting  the exercise will take place for the second time away from the Bihar capital.        
	The officials engaged in arranging Nitishs week-long trip at the Rajgir circuit house, however, said the chief minister was in a holiday mood at the end of the year. He would be away from political leaders and busy schedule of Patna at the years end, said a senior official, adding that he would begin his routine work at Patna in the New Year. Observers believe that Nitish was willing to repeat Barbighi at Rajgir to reap benefits in 2010 polls.                                                                                                                                                          
